```

The loop condition `i < items.length - 1` makes the loop exit one iteration too early, so `items[items.length - 1]` (the last element) is never pushed into `results`.

**Change:** Remove `- 1` from the loop bound in `src/utils.ts`. That single character change is all that's needed — the existing test suite in `tests/utils.test.ts` already covers all the relevant cases (3-item array, single item, two items, empty array) and will pass once the fix is applied.
